Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.42,0:01:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm terribly sorry,\NYour Excellency.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.79,0:01:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a country road for\Nquite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.59,0:01:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.76,0:01:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm perfectly satisfied...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.49,0:01:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,...with this beautiful\Ndisplay of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.83,0:01:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's no need\Nto worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.70,0:01:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a defeated man,\Nand no longer your leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.90,0:01:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.87,0:01:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this area all belong\Nto the Romefeller Foundation?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.31,0:01:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.51,0:01:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Initially, the Romefeller\NFoundation...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.51,0:01:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,...used its financial power\Nto protect this beautiful area.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.48,0:02:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My support for that attitude...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.22,0:02:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,...is precisely why I built\Nthe "Specials" unit...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.92,0:02:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,...within the United Earth\NSphere Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.09,0:02:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then those young warriors\Nwith rebellious wings...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.03,0:02:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,...placed themselves before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.69,0:02:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Gundams: the mobile suits made from\NGundanium alloy...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.85,0:02:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,...and sent from the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.69,0:02:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The high-level pilots of\Nthese Gundams...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.36,0:02:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,...soon challenged me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.97,0:03:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Wu Fei!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.71,0:03:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Treize Khushrenada.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.16,0:03:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The duel is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.23,0:03:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.24,0:03:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That strength and bravery\Nwas exceptional.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.94,0:03:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I was moved by every\Naction they took...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.48,0:03:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,...and could not remain still.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.28,0:03:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it was the same\Nfor you, Zechs Merquise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.35,0:03:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you should fight\Nwith a pure heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.75,0:03:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,...to achieve your goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.30,0:03:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Set the Sanc Kingdom\Nfree from the Alliance's grasp.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.04,0:04:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}All mobile suits have{\i0}\N{\i1}left the carriers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.34,0:04:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll leave too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.01,0:04:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll be backing you up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.78,0:04:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Concentrate only on achieving{\i0}\N{\i1}your mission, Lieutenant Zechs.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.58,0:04:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm totally focused.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.58,0:04:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The new type of mobile suit{\i0}\N{\i1}is approaching fast!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.05,0:04:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Direct all laser beams{\i0}\N{\i1}at that suit!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.82,0:04:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It took me 13 years to\Nreturn to these grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.02,0:04:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Please forgive me, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.66,0:05:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There's been much bloodshed\Nalong the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.30,0:05:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,...and I've only been able\Nto live a lifestyle...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.90,0:05:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,...that counters your\Npacifist teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.37,0:05:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My hands are too stained\Nwith blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.61,0:05:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm completely unfit to head\Nthe Peacecraft monarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.71,0:05:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure she would\Nbe able to head the country...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.98,0:05:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,...as you'd intended.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.68,0:05:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll fight to make that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.32,0:05:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I've failed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.95,0:05:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Please forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.72,0:05:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,By appearing on the\Ncenter stage of history...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.59,0:05:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,...we directed the times\Nin the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.46,0:05:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The remaining frontier\Nis outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.06,0:05:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Une, I'm leaving outer\Nspace in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.84,0:05:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Explain our love to the\Npeople of the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.71,0:05:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure they'll be able\Nto understand us...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.14,0:05:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,...if you greet them with\Nyour affection.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.51,0:05:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In the year After Colony 195...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.22,0:05:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,...the United Earth Sphere\NAlliance collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.72,0:06:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the Alliance's forces\Nremained in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.89,0:06:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In charge of outer space...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.42,0:06:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,...my mission was to\Nsubjugate these forces...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.63,0:06:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,...free the colonies, and allow\Nthem to become independent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.63,0:06:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Once this was accomplished...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.70,0:06:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,...we should have achieved\NTreize's and our ideals for OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.47,0:06:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If only Treize and Duke\NDermail hadn't disagreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.64,0:06:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gundam pilots witnessed\Nthe changes in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.88,0:06:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Transmission from Earth,{\i0}\N{\i1}Colonel Une!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.35,0:06:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Gundams Zero Two and Zero Four are attacking{\i0}\N{\i1}the Singapore Space Port Base!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.89,0:06:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm returning to the\Ncommand tower!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.47,0:06:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, Quatre!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.90,0:06:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.60,0:06:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll back you two up\Nuntil you lift off!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.97,0:06:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you lost your mind?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.01,0:06:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We all have to make it\Nup to outer space!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.58,0:06:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I know, but that's why I\N{\i1}have to back you up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.08,0:06:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}To make sure that at least{\i0}\N{\i1}you two make it!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.38,0:07:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.45,0:07:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You fool!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.05,0:07:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, the last remaining\Nchoice is to self-detonate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.44,0:07:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.67,0:07:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're telling me to get off?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.37,0:07:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Sandrock!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.82,0:07:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, my dear Sandrock!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.10,0:07:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was neither glory\Nnor praise to greet them...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.40,0:07:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,...when they returned to\Nouter space.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.41,0:08:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All they got was isolation...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.58,0:08:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,...and a cruel destiny fitting\Nfor such rebels.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.80,0:08:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have to considerably\Nrestrict your activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.01,0:08:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,For defeated men like myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.81,0:08:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,...restrictions become the\Nfoundation for new strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.64,0:08:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But in my case I feel\Nmuch freer, not restricted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.81,0:08:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps until now I didn't\Nexperience freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.82,0:08:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe my latest move\Nhas allowed me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.29,0:08:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,...a chance to step back\Nand re-evaluate myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.79,0:08:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like you overcame\Nthe ordeal I put you through...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.60,0:08:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,...and earned your\Nfreedom, Zechs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.97,0:08:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize, stop following me\Naround!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.56,0:09:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I can no longer be your friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.26,0:09:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Farewell, Treize!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.53,0:09:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,After you left...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.17,0:09:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,...with Chief Engineer\NTubarov at the helm...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.40,0:09:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,...Romefeller completed\Nthose mobile dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.07,0:09:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,...that are incapable of feeling\Na battle's beauty or sorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.71,0:09:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Romefeller used them...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.15,0:09:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,...to try ruling the Earth\Nfrom outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.18,0:09:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,As one who looks for\Nmeaning in human battles...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.45,0:09:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,...I couldn't accept the\NFoundation's way of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.16,0:09:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs, without you OZ\Nends up allowing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.46,0:10:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,...worthless actions by\Nworthless people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.51,0:10:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Very nicely done,\NTreize Khushrenada!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.97,0:10:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The people in space are\Nclose to accepting OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.71,0:10:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.08,0:10:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And Colonel Une's achievements\Nhave been impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.15,0:10:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,She's forming friendly relations\Nwith one colony after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.25,0:10:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The sense of independence\Nbuilt by forming a nation...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.29,0:10:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,...will trigger a desire for\Nproductivity and defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.39,0:10:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This leads to the nation\Nbecoming militaristic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.23,0:10:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means that every\Ncountry on the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.56,0:10:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,...will jump into OZ's arms\Nand beg to be governed by us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.67,0:10:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beautiful Treize.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.44,0:10:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You've made space a member\Nof the Romefeller Foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.51,0:10:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The living environment\Nof the colonies is bogus.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.11,0:10:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As is their pacifism.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.98,0:10:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They may only be a hotbed\Nleading to countless battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.81,0:10:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs...or rather Milliardo...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.58,0:10:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Had you already realized that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.96,0:11:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The new system since OZ and\Nthe colonies became united...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.90,0:11:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,...has had a considerable\Ninfluence on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.03,0:11:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,On behalf of my nation...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.67,0:11:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,...I've come to find out\Nabout this situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.44,0:11:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Your nation?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.77,0:11:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.11,0:11:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come here from the\NSanc Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.01,0:11:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Milliardo Peacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.88,0:11:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, His Excellency has had\Nties with the Sanc Kingdom...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.21,0:11:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,...since his youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.85,0:11:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard your nation was\Nrecovering from the wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.92,0:11:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I understand\Nthe implications of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.06,0:11:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought I could\Ngive advice...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.56,0:11:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,...to the colonies desiring\Nmilitary power.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.13,0:11:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many ways\Nto obtain peace for oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.76,0:11:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Between us, we'll find\Nthe best direction to take.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.37,0:11:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You might be on the\Nright track to peace...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.54,0:11:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,...Representative Lady Une.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.51,0:11:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My beloved Lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.51,0:11:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You were right all along...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.46,0:12:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as mankind\Nexists in this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.79,0:12:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,...there will always be battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.66,0:12:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And denouncing battles\Nwill never lead to peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.20,0:12:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's natural for this world\Nto continue fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.15,0:12:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.38,0:12:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs and the Gundam pilots\Nare making an effort...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.39,0:12:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,...to construct a new future.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.59,0:12:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Those that fight have\Na sense of fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.53,0:12:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And those in actual combat\Nare not seen as being tainted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.63,0:12:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A human life is more precious\Nthan anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.07,0:12:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It is because one faces\Nan enemy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.77,0:12:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,...and risks his own\Nprecious life...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.84,0:12:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,...that amid all the sorrow,\Na warrior's soul shines nobly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.08,0:13:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Tag along, on my\Njourney into hell!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.92,0:13:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Pure and genuine\NGundam pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.58,0:13:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,As I've repeatedly seen\Nthe way you fought...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.15,0:13:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,...I couldn't help but\Nfeel inspired.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.69,0:13:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You changed something\Ninside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.66,0:13:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Even altered my destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.30,0:13:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Nataku.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.23,0:13:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to become\Na lot stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.77,0:13:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When the foolish Romefeller\NFoundation...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.74,0:13:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,...removed the human aspect\Nfrom battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.57,0:13:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I might have suddenly\Nfound myself in a position...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.18,0:13:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,...where I must personally\Nbury OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.58,0:13:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But the times have entrusted\Nthe pilots with destiny itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.02,0:13:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Young warriors.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.45,0:13:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you see beyond this\Ndark mass of confusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.40,0:13:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They continue to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.64,0:14:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,These youngsters who'll\Nchange the times.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.72,0:14:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize is hoping we'll\Nput up a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.69,0:14:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no choice left\Nbut to battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.76,0:14:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Without fighting, nothing\Ncan be created.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.30,0:14:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.17,0:14:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.98,0:14:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Zechs Merquise...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.61,0:14:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or rather, my eternal friend,{\i0}\N{\i1}Milliardo Peacecraft.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.72,0:14:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ is changing, and I'm\Nsorely lacking in power.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.89,0:14:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Romefeller's way, or rather...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.29,0:14:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,...the path that mankind is\Ntaking, is too selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.19,0:14:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm shocked to see...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.63,0:15:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...that their increased power made{\i0}\N{\i1}them abandon their compassion.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.46,0:15:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Milliardo, there's one other\Nperson who understands me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.37,0:15:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Her feelings toward me have\Ngiven her split personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.04,0:15:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I implore you, Milliardo.\NPlease save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.65,0:15:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to fight for Treize...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.01,0:15:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,...to help realize his ideal!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.66,0:15:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.69,0:15:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got no power.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.73,0:15:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In the confusion of\Nall these battles...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.13,0:15:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,...I can only walk the\Npath of a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.33,0:15:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Take me to Fortress Barge.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.11,0:15:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when I realized\Nthe purpose of battles...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.65,0:15:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,...isn't limited to making\Nideals into reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.72,0:15:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I know this was what\NTreize wanted me to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.12,0:16:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Botched your mission?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.76,0:16:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't destroy the base...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.23,0:16:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,...and you didn't kill\NDr. J and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.70,0:16:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't rub it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.57,0:16:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still glad I decided\Nto come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.54,0:16:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.01,0:16:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Gundam and mine\Nare being rebuilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.28,0:16:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hardly wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.25,0:16:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.78,0:16:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be the God of Death again!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.15,0:16:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.59,0:16:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.59,0:16:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,...good night...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.76,0:16:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if the Space Colonies\Nhave no reason to retaliate...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.76,0:16:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,...and the pilots are captured\Nand stripped of their suits...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.03,0:16:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,...those Gundam pilots\Nwill continue to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.97,0:16:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.41,0:16:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.11,0:16:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Trowa.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.74,0:16:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Outer space has gone mad{\i0}\N{\i1}so I'll destroy it all.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.51,0:17:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the others for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.98,0:17:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them to stay away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.32,0:17:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm telling you not{\i0}\N{\i1}to get any closer!!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.11,0:17:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What strong will.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.25,0:17:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And what purity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.52,0:17:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We must fight against\Neach other.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.62,0:17:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But our desire to fight\Nis the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.92,0:17:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Good-bye, Heero.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.60,0:17:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa, escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.93,0:17:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The Vayeate's gonna explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.10,0:17:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.98,0:18:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.15,0:18:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We have to acknowledge{\i0}\N{\i1}the facts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.12,0:18:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The five of us have become\Nredundant soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.80,0:18:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.44,0:18:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Duke Dermail.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.14,0:18:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't support the Romefeller\NFoundation's current path.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.31,0:18:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.41,0:18:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe that what mankind\Nneeds is not absolute victory...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.98,0:18:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,...but his attitude toward\Nfighting; his demeanor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.39,0:18:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,An era constructed by the\Nsoulless weapons...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.52,0:18:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,...known as mobile dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.29,0:18:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,...will become an embarrassment\Nto future generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.56,0:18:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The traditions you value\Nso highly...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.36,0:18:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,...would be blurred alongside\Nthose five genuine warriors.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.00,0:19:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.64,0:19:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're saying that you want\NRomefeller headquarters...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.67,0:19:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,...to take OZ out of\Nyour control?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.28,0:19:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I hereby confine you to\NRomefeller headquarters!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.12,0:19:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I have come to a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.82,0:19:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll look over those young\Nmen who shine in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.22,0:19:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll love them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.69,0:19:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I fail to understand\Nwhat you're getting at.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.70,0:19:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why you\Nand I are enemies!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.24,0:19:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna escape?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.61,0:19:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,After we pay them back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.16,0:19:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Une, my love.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.83,0:19:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Rest in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.14,0:20:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond those distant\Nshining stars...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.41,0:20:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,...I see many destinies pass\Nby each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.64,0:20:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Time goes by so fast\Nand fleetingly...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.75,0:20:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,...from my memories of those\Nolden days.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.08,0:20:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Operation Nova.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.25,0:20:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine the\NRomefeller Foundation...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.35,0:20:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,...allowing the rebellions of\Nthe soldiers that support me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.36,0:20:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And now they have sent\Nmass-produced Virgo dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.56,0:20:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,...to Earth in their quest for\Nits complete control.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.97,0:20:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But right now, I have no\Nright to express these opinions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.28,0:20:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.99,0:20:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.59,0:21:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.61,0:21:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.55,0:21:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Discarding his Gundam\Nlike that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.09,0:21:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What was he thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.66,0:21:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.82,0:21:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The foundation of our future\Nwill be built by these suits.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.20,0:21:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, casting for the\Nactors is almost complete...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.80,0:21:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,...as we begin the third act.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.74,0:21:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,All that's left is to wait\Nfor the curtain to rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.35,0:22:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.62,0:22:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is proceeding\Njust as you planned, Treize.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.79,0:23:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Outer space rushes aimlessly\Ninto a period of battles.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.73,0:23:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero and Quatre arrive\Non Earth and are targeted...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.49,0:23:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,...by Romefeller's plan to\Nexecute the Gundam pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.40,0:23:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Without any time to rest...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.93,0:23:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,...Heero heads to gather data\Nfor his next battle...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.84,0:23:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,...when he hears of Sanc\NKingdom, Relena's home country.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.54,0:23:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, on Gundam Wing, Episode 29,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.92,0:23:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Heroine of the Battlefield".
